Uses of Package
com.cyc.kb.exception

  • Packages that use com.cyc.kb.exception 
    Package Description
    com.cyc.kb
    Provides basic interfaces for manipulating CycL-based java objects, both for the purpose of making assertions and for retrieving terms and values via simple queries.
    com.cyc.kb.client
    The implementation of various interfaces specified in com.cyc.kb, refer to that package for a more detailed discussion of using the API.
    com.cyc.kb.exception
    This package contains the exception hierarchy in the KB API.
    com.cyc.kb.quant
    Provides quantifications, not fully supported in 1.0.0-Preview release, and subject to change.
    com.cyc.km.modeling.task
    Provides the classes for representing and working with tasks.
    com.cyc.query
    Provides the core classes for constructing, specifying, and running Cyc queries.
  • Classes in com.cyc.kb.exception used by com.cyc.kb 
    Class and Description
    CreateException
    Thrown when code fails to find or create something from the Cyc KB.
    DeleteException
    Thrown when code fails to delete something from the Cyc KB.
    InvalidNameException
    Thrown when code attempts to create a KB entity with an invalid name.
    KBApiException
    Root class for exceptions thrown by the KB API.
    KBTypeConflictException
    Thrown when an entity exists in the KB, but is incompatible with a particular semantic object type.
    KBTypeException
    Thrown when an entity exists in the KB, but does not currently meet the requirements of a particular semantic object type.
    VariableArityException
    Thrown when the arity a Relation without a fixed arity is requested.
